      "correct": "This is the Fundamental Attribution Error - the tendency to overemphasize dispositional (personality-based) explanations while underestimating situational influences. Participants attributed the questioner's advantage to superior general knowledge (dispositional) rather than to their role advantage of creating questions (situational).",
      "incorrect": {
        "False Consensus Effect": "False Consensus Effect involves overestimating how many others share your views/behaviors, not about attribution of others' abilities.",
